econd time scales. The theory is illustrated with\nseveral applications to one-dimensional semiconductor quantum wires and\nsuperlattices, double quantum dots, semiconductor and graphene quantum rings.\nFurthermore, we consider the response of strongly correlated systems to short\nbroadband pulses and show that this case bears a great potential to unveil high\norder correlations while they build up upon excitations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Mar 2016 17:00:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 22 Nov 2016 18:39:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-02-15"}
