{"id":"1603.07131","submitter":"Maciej Capinski","authors":"Maciej J. Capinski, Piotr Zgliczynski","title":"Beyond the Melnikov method: a computer assisted approach","comments":"54 pages, 10 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.DS","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We present a Melnikov type approach for establishing transversal\nintersections of stable/unstable manifolds of perturbed normally hyperbolic\ninvariant manifolds (NHIMs). The method is based on a new geometric proof of\nthe normally hyperbolic invariant manifold theorem, which establishes the\nexistence of a NHIM, together with its associated invariant manifolds and\nbounds on their first and second derivatives. We do not need to know the\nexplicit formulas for the homoclinic orbits prior to the perturbation. We also\ndo not need to compute any integrals along such homoclinics. All needed bounds\nare established using rigorous computer assisted numerics. Lastly, and most\nimportantly, the method establishes intersections for an explicit range of\nparameters, and not only for perturbations that are `small enough', as is the\ncase in the classical Melnikov approach.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 23 Mar 2016 10:57:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-24"}
